{
  "stem": "2581.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But, of course, you could say it with strangers, but my father was-- couldn't wait for the minute we would have it in our family, and he never lived-- he never lived to this moment.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I remember when, on August 30-- no, August 31, it was a Thursday-- we went from HaNoar HaTzioni, and had a thing, what was called a scout war, where you go into the woods, two groups that are wearing different colored scarf ties.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the purpose is if you tap someone-- if you touch the shoulder-- he's got to give you his tie.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was that kind of war.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we came back and it was already little dark, but we saw on the walls the sign, mobilization.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were so happy we're were going to see a real war.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Children, you know, are excited they're going to see a real war.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The very next day, September 1, there were already dead people in our town.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right, because we were pretty close-- pretty close to the German border.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And soldiers, or individuals, would walk on the bridge and planes would come down.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you know, just-- they were looking-- the German planes were flying to see-- what are these called?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The hunter planes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they saw people on the bridge, so they shot them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't know if they were Jewish or not Jewish.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But that was-- and on that the following Sunday-- the following Sunday, which was September the 3rd, we were-- the sirens were, you know, were on, because it was an alarm that the German planes are coming on.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we were hiding in the cornfield, small cornfield.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And a stupid Polish policeman picked up a rifle and tried to shoot with a rifle to the plane.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
